-- Bank Asya, Turkish finance ministry tax collection accord cancelled
-- By Orhan Coskun
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 06:38AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 7 (Reuters) - An agreement between the Turkish Finance Ministry and Islamic lender Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS> allowing the bank to collect taxes has been cancelled, the revenue adminstration said on its web site.

The bank was notified that the agreement will be annulled as of Sept. 8, it said.